==English==

===Etymology===
From Latin ''[[donare]]'' (to give).

===Pronunciation===
*Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-eɪt|-eɪt]]

===Verb===
{{en-verb|donat|ing}}

#To give away something of value to support or contribute towards something.
#:''She donates 100 dollars to Red Crescent every year.''
#:''He donated an etching from his own collection to the new art gallery.''

